The paper proposes a caching policy that uses a feedforward neural network to predict content popularity. This involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity and Cryptography), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
